Dear @ChrisCuomo: Thank you for asking the question about the legal standard. For the Obstruction of Justice statute, a person is guilty if they "endeavor" to obstruct justice. Actual interference (or punching) is not required. https://twitter.com/NewDay/status/1119218110735585281 QT @NewDay Analyzing the Mueller report, @ChrisCuomo says: "Asking matters Jim. If I ask you to punch Mr. Meadows and you don't do it, the request was still wrong."

@RepMarkMeadows: "The request may have been wrong but it's not a crime unless he assaults me"

Cuomo: "Is that our standard?" http://pbs.twimg.com/media/D4hC7yQUcAA36s5.jpg https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/1119217871706447872/vid/320x180/F1ZqmQzQRCqI_iOl.mp4?tag=11

